George Perle (May 6, 1915 – January 23, 2009) was a composer and music theorist.
George Perle (May 6, 1915 – January 23, 2009) was a composer and music theorist.
He earned his doctorate at New York University in 1956.Perle composed with a technique of his own devising called "twelve-tone tonality".
Basically this creates a hierarchy among the notes of the chromatic scale so that they are all referentially related to one or two pitches which then function as a tonic note or chord in tonality.
